		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Introduction to general relativity</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is intended as an accessible, non-technical introduction to the subject. For the main encyclopedia article, see <a href="/wiki/General_relativity" title="General relativity">General relativity</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Cassini-science-br.jpg" class="image" title="High-precision test of general relativity by the Cassini space probe (artist's impression): radio signals sent between the Earth and the probe (green wave) are delayed by the warping of space and time (blue lines) due to the Sun's mass."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Cassini-science-br.jpg/250px-Cassini-science-br.jpg" width="250" height="361" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Cassini-science-br.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
High-precision test of general relativity by the <a href="/wiki/Cassini-Huygens" title="Cassini-Huygens" class="mw-redirect">Cassini</a> space probe (artist's impression): <a href="/wiki/Radio" title="Radio">radio</a> signals sent between the Earth and the probe (green wave) are <a href="/wiki/Shapiro_effect" title="Shapiro effect" class="mw-redirect">delayed</a> by the warping of <a href="/wiki/Space_and_time" title="Space and time" class="mw-redirect">space and time</a> (blue lines) due to the <a href="/wiki/Sun" title="Sun">Sun</a>'s mass.</div>
